rComments: Mendelsohn is a little eccentric, a little weird. He makes concepts clear, but he makes frequent errors on the board: mislabeling variables and so on. However, if you process everything before writing it in your notes, you can use his errors as a way to ensure that you understand the material well.
Very lazy, very unorganized, take 20 mins to look up the textbook and give an example on board.  Assignments take forever to mark.
